page.title: 06continued
page.content: The chancel has plain eaves.The east window of the chancel is early 14th century work of three tredfoiled lights with quatrefoiled net tracery. Near the south door is a modern font. There is a 15th century rood-screen in five bays with tracery.In the chancel are two 17th century oak armchairs, and a Jacobean table in the vestry.The oldest Memorial slab in the chancel is 1675 to Sir Humphrey Monoux.The belfry contains six bells.Several relics of Roman art have been found in the churchyard.The first known vicar was in 1258 John of Dunstable.The present vicar and Rural Dean of Bedford is the Very Reverend Mr.John Kirkby.
